    <h1 id="work-history-header" class="header work-history">
      Work History
    </h1>
      <ul class="lists" style="list-style-type:none">
        <li style="font-size:18px">United Electronic Industries Inc.</li>
        <li style="font-size:11px">March 2022 - Present</li>
        <li stlye="font-size:100px">Computer Engineering Project Planner</li>
      </ul>
      Essential Elements:<br>
      <ul>
        <li>Work with the engineering and design validation teams to create and maintain up-to-date schedules for project development and release.</li>
        <li>Perform risk and critical path analysis, provide routine status reports, and estimate release dates.</li>
        <li>Assist Director of Engineering to keep projects on schedule.</li>
        <li>Assist engineering team to adhere it its own process and established standards.</li>
        <li>Create and maintain master schedule to establish sequence and lead time of deliverables.</li>
        <li>Communicate with manufacturing to schedule prototype and pilot builds according to project plans and maintain status of prototype builds.</li>
        <li>Tracks costs of each project on monthly basis.</li>
        <li>Monitor schedule compliance levels and identify reasons for completion delays.</li>
        <li>Evaluate current procedures and recommend changes to improve the efficiency of planning and scheduling of projects.</li>
        <li>Perform general administrative office functions in support of the Director of Engineering to accomplish engineering team objectives.</li>
        <li>Work with engineers to manage materials, prototypes, and engineering units.</li>
      </ul>
      
    </p>
   
